claim.claim-text:
8. A jewelry piece comprising:
(a) a band having first and second ends;
(b) a bezel having an outside wall comprising a top section, a bottom section and a recessed center section around the circumference of the exterior wall, an open top, an open bottom, and an inside wall defining a lumen extending between said open top and open bottom, and a lumen wall having a seat, and at least one recess;
(c) the bezel bottom section secured to the first end of the band, a hook formed at said second end of the band;
(d) a stone positioned at least partially within said lumen and in contact with said seat; and
(e) a seat bead positioned within said recess cooperating with said seat to hold said stone to said bezel,
wherein said hook receives said recessed center section of said bezel to secure said first and second portions of said band together.
